 new environment\".",[12,511,512],{},[15,513],{"alt":514,"src":515},"Create a new environment","https:\u002F\u002Fimages.israynotarray.com\u002FblogImg\u002Fother\u002Fmockoon\u002F%E6%88%AA%E5%9C%96%202023-03-07%2016.33.49.png",[12,517,518],{},"Give it a name (e.g., Todolist-example), pick a path, and hit \"Create\".",[12,520,521],{},[15,522],{"alt":523,"src":524},"Todolist-example","https:\u002F\u002Fimages.israynotarray.com\u002FblogImg\u002Fother\u002Fmockoon\u002F%E6%88%AA%E5%9C%96%202023-03-07%2016.34.11.png",[12,526,527],{},"The new environment shows up in Mockoon's sidebar.",[12,529,530],{},[15,531],{"alt":523,"src":532},"https:\u002F\u002Fimages.israynotarray.com\u002FblogImg\u002Fother\u002Fmockoon\u002F%E6%88%AA%E5%9C%96%202023-03-07%2016.35.48.png",[12,534,535,536,539],{},"Quick note — see that ",[128,537,538],{},"localhost:3001"," at the bottom? That's the URL the Mock API will be served on. You can change it later if you want, but leave it for now.",[541,542,544],"h4",{"id":543},"export-environment","Export environment",[12,546,547],{},"If you want to share your environment with someone else, right-click and pick \"Show in folder\" — Mockoon stores environments as JSON files, just hand the JSON over.",[12,549,550],{},[15,551],{"alt":552,"src":553},"Export","https:\u002F\u002Fimages.israynotarray.com\u002FblogImg\u002Fother\u002Fmockoon\u002F202303071751.jpg",[541,555,557],{"id":556},"import-environment","Import environment",[12,559,560],{},"Whoever receives the JSON clicks the folder icon at the top (\"Open an environment\") and drops in the file.",[12,562,563],{},[15,564],{"alt":565,"src":566},"Import","https:\u002F\u002Fimages.israynotarray.com\u002FblogImg\u002Fother\u002Fmockoon\u002F%E6%88%AA%E5%9C%96%202023-03-07%2017.52.01.png",[503,568,570],{"id":569},"create-a-mock-api","Create a Mock API",[12,572,573],{},"Click \"TodoList-example\" in the sidebar — you should see this:",[12,575,576],{},[15,577],{"alt":578,"src":579},"TodoList-example","https:\u002F\u002Fimages.israynotarray.com\u002FblogImg\u002Fother\u002Fmockoon\u002F%E6%88%AA%E5%9C%96%202023-03-07%2016.42.38.png",[12,581,582],{},"Click the arrow at the top — three things you can create:",[584,585,586,590,593],"ul",{},[587,588,589],"li",{},"CRUD Route",[587,591,592],{},"HTTP Route",[587,594,595],{},"Folder",[12,597,598],{},"CRUD Route generates a full CRUD API for you. HTTP Route is a custom route you define yourself. Folder is for organizing — e.g., put all the TodoList routes under one folder.",[12,600,601],{},"We're going with HTTP Route, so pick that. The right pane is where you fill in the API details.",[12,603,604],{},[15,605],{"alt":606,"src":607},"API details","https:\u002F\u002Fimages.israynotarray.com\u002FblogImg\u002Fother\u002Fmockoon\u002F%E6%88%AA%E5%9C%96%202023-03-07%2016.51.26.png",[12,609,610],{},"Here's a field-by-field translation, with the example filled in:",[12,612,613],{},[15,614],{"alt":615,"src":616},"Field reference","https:\u002F\u002Fimages.israynotarray.com\u002FblogImg\u002Fother\u002Fmockoon\u002F202303071700.jpg",[12,618,619],{},"Following the spec doc, your screen should look like this:",[12,621,622],{},[15,623],{"alt":606,"src":624},"https:\u002F\u002Fimages.israynotarray.com\u002FblogImg\u002Fother\u002Fmockoon\u002F%E6%88%AA%E5%9C%96%202023-03-07%2017.04.23.png",[12,626,627],{},"One route done. Now build the rest yourself. When you're done, your route list looks like this:",[12,629,630],{},[15,631],{"alt":632,"src":633},"Route list","https:\u002F\u002Fimages.israynotarray.com\u002FblogImg\u002Fother\u002Fmockoon\u002F%E6%88%AA%E5%9C%96%202023-03-07%2017.18.42.png",[541,635,637],{"id":636},"multiple-responses","Multiple responses",[12,639,640],{},"Mockoon also supports multiple responses per route — handy for testing different scenarios. Build a 200 response and a 500 response, and switch between them to test how your frontend handles each. Click here to add:",[12,642,643],{},[15,644],{"alt":637,"src":645},"https:\u002F\u002Fimages.israynotarray.com\u002FblogImg\u002Fother\u002Fmockoon\u002F%E6%88%AA%E5%9C%96%202023-03-07%2017.54.32.png",[503,647,649],{"id":648},"start-the-mock-api","Start the Mock API",[12,651,652],{},"Time to fire it up — the start button is here:",[12,654,655],{},[15,656],{"alt":657,"src":658},"Start button","https:\u002F\u002Fimages.israynotarray.com\u002FblogImg\u002Fother\u002Fmockoon\u002F%E6%88%AA%E5%9C%96%202023-03-07%2017.25.26.png",[12,660,661],{},"But before launching, two settings to tweak — otherwise your frontend will hit issues integrating.",[541,663,665],{"id":664},"change-the-port","Change the Port",[12,667,668],{},"Click \"TodoList-example\", then the \"Setting\" button on the right.",[12,670,671],{},[15,672],{"alt":673,"src":674},"Setting","https:\u002F\u002Fimages.israynotarray.com\u002FblogImg\u002Fother\u002Fmockoon\u002F%E6%88%AA%E5%9C%96%202023-03-07%2017.32.11.png",[12,676,677],{},"If you don't like port 3001, switch it to 3000. The new port takes effect as soon as you start.",[12,679,680],{},[15,681],{"alt":682,"src":683},"Port","https:\u002F\u002Fimages.israynotarray.com\u002FblogImg\u002Fother\u002Fmockoon\u002F%E6%88%AA%E5%9C%96%202023-03-07%2017.34.57.png",[541,685,687],{"id":686},"set-up-cors","Set up CORS",[12,689,690],{},"Now click the Headers tab at the top, then the \"Add CORS header\" button.",[12,692,693],{},[15,694],{"alt":695,"src":696},"CORS","https:\u002F\u002Fimages.israynotarray.com\u002FblogImg\u002Fother\u002Fmockoon\u002F%E6%88%AA%E5%9C%96%202023-03-07%2017.36.46.png",[12,698,699],{},"Mockoon auto-fills the right CORS headers.",[12,701,702],{},[15,703],{"alt":695,"src":704},"https:\u002F\u002Fimages.israynotarray.com\u002FblogImg\u002Fother\u002Fmockoon\u002F%E6%88%AA%E5%9C%96%202023-03-07%2017.37.59.png",[12,706,707],{},"Now you can start Mockoon and integrate against it from your frontend without browser blocks.",[541,709,711],{"id":710},"calling-the-api-and-viewing-logs","Calling the API and viewing logs",[12,