peat 5}}"," repeat 5 times",[587,1127,1128,1131],{},[128,1129,1130],{},"{{guid}}"," random GUID",[587,1133,1134,1137],{},[128,1135,1136],{},"{{lorem 5}}"," 5 lorem ipsum words",[587,1139,1140,1143],{},[128,1141,1142],{},"{{boolean}}"," random true\u002Ffalse",[587,1145,1146,1149],{},[128,1147,1148],{},"{{\u002Frepeat}}"," end of repeat",[12,1151,1152,1153,1158],{},"These are Mockoon's wrapped helpers. For the full list, check the ",[75,1154,1157],{"href":1155,"rel":1156},"https:\u002F\u002Fmockoon.com\u002Fdocs\u002Flatest\u002Ftemplating\u002Fmockoon-helpers\u002F#objectid",[79],"Mockoon templating helpers"," docs.",[20,1160,1162],{"id":1161},"mockoon-crud","Mockoon CRUD",[12,1164,1165],{},"Some of you might be wondering — what about POST or PUT? Can Mockoon actually simulate full CRUD? Yes, Mockoon has CRUD routes for that. I haven't played with them deeply myself, so just point you at the docs:",[12,1167,1168],{},[75,1169,1172],{"href":1170,"rel":1171},"https:\u002F\u002Fmockoon.com\u002Fdocs\u002Flatest\u002Fapi-endpoints\u002Fcrud-routes\u002F",[79],"CRUD routes",[20,1174,1176],{"id":1175},"closing-thoughts","Closing thoughts",[12,1178,1179],{},"Mockoon is a tool I reach for a lot. When the backend can't ship endpoints in time, I just ask them to send the spec first, build the Mock API in Mockoon, then swap to real endpoints when backend's done — clean switch. Mockoon starts and stops quickly, and the GUI is straightforward. Solid tool.",[1181,1182,1183],"style",{},"html pre.shiki code .s-VM4, html code.shiki .s-VM4{--shiki-default:#91CBFF;--shiki-default-font-weight:bold}html pre.shiki code .sMAXC, html code.shiki .sMAXC{--shiki-default:#F0F3F6}html .default .shiki span {color: var(--shiki-default);background: var(--shiki-default-bg);font-style: var(--shiki-default-font-style);font-weight: var(--shiki-default-font-weight);text-decoration: var(--shiki-default-text-decoration);}html .shiki span {color: var(--shiki-default);background: var(--shiki-default-bg);fon